---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionDivider from '@components/SectionDivider.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy & data collection"
  description="What data this site collects, why, and how to opt out. We collect anonymous province and visit length only with your consent. No IP addresses, no cookies, no third-party trackers."
  lang={lang}
  articleWidth
>
  <article class="prose-content py-8">
    <SectionDivider />
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy & data collection</h1>
    <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-8">Last updated: 2026-04-29</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">The short version</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      We collect <strong>nothing about you by default</strong>. If you click "Allow" on the
      privacy banner, we collect two pieces of anonymous, aggregate information:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc ms-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>Your <strong>governorate (province)</strong> inside Iraq — derived once per pageview, never stored alongside your IP.</li>
      <li>How long your visit lasts, in seconds.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      That is the entire list. No name. No email. No IP address kept. No cookies. No tracking
      across visits. No advertising. No social media pixels. No fingerprinting. No session
      replays. We never sell, share, or transfer this data to anyone.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Why we collect anything at all</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      We want to know whether this site is reaching people inside Iraq, which governorates
      need more outreach, and whether visitors are actually reading guides or bouncing in
      seconds. We cannot make the site useful without some signal. We picked the smallest
      possible signal that still tells us this.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">How it works (technical detail)</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Analytics are off by default. The first time you visit, you see a banner asking
      whether to allow analytics. Your choice is saved in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>
      under the key <code>ispc-analytics</code>. If you decline, no analytics script ever loads.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      If you allow, we load <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy" class="text-terracotta underline">Plausible Analytics</a>,
      an open-source, EU-hosted service that:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc ms-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>Does <strong>not</strong> store IP addresses. Your IP is used only in memory to look up your
        country/region, then immediately discarded.</li>
      <li>Does <strong>not</strong> use cookies or any persistent identifier.</li>
      <li>Cannot link visits across days. There is no way to recognize you returning.</li>
      <li>Is hosted in the European Union, under GDPR jurisdiction.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      We separately fire one event when your visit ends, with the duration in seconds. That
      event also contains no identifier.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">What we don't do</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc ms-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>We do not log IP addresses, ever, anywhere.</li>
      <li>We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook, TikTok, or any advertising tracker.</li>
      <li>We do not use cookies of any kind.</li>
      <li>We do not embed YouTube, Twitter, Instagram, or any third-party content that could leak data.</li>
      <li>We do not require an account or email to use this site.</li>
      <li>We do not share data with any government, party, NGO, or company.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">How to opt out (or opt back in)</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Click the button below to change your choice at any time. The change takes effect
      immediately and only affects this browser on this device.
    </p>
    <div id="ispc-analytics-status-block" class="my-6 p-4 border border-navy/20 bg-cream/40">
      <p id="ispc-analytics-status" class="font-semibold mb-3">—</p>
      <button
        type="button"
        id="ispc-analytics-toggle"
        class="px-4 py-2 bg-navy text-cream font-semibold text-sm cursor-pointer hover:bg-navy/90"
      >
        Change
      </button>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">If you have stronger threat-model needs</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      If you are at high risk and want zero data leaving your device — even anonymously —
      <strong>decline analytics</strong> and use a VPN. Browser-side, you can also block
      <code>plausible.io</code> in your hosts file or content blocker. The site will continue
      to work normally.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Other data flows worth knowing</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc ms-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Quick Exit</strong> opens <code>google.com</code> in a new tab and replaces this
        site with <code>google.com</code> in your tab — by design, so the site is removed from
        your back button. Google sees a hit at that moment.</li>
      <li><strong>Fonts</strong> are served from this site, not from Google Fonts or any CDN.</li>
      <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> this site is hosted on GitHub Pages. GitHub's infrastructure
        sees standard HTTP request metadata (IP, user-agent) like any web server. We have no
        access to those logs and do not retain them.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      If you have questions or want to request that nothing of yours appears in our
      aggregate stats, contact us via the methods on the
      <a href="/en/community" class="text-terracotta underline">community page</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    (function () {
      try {
        var KEY = 'ispc-analytics';
        var status = document.getElementById('ispc-analytics-status');
        var btn = document.getElementById('ispc-analytics-toggle');
        if (!status || !btn) return;
        function render() {
          var v = null;
          try { v = localStorage.getItem(KEY); } catch (e) {}
          if (v === 'true') {
            status.textContent = 'Anonymous analytics: ON';
            btn.textContent = 'Turn off';
          } else {
            status.textContent = 'Anonymous analytics: OFF';
            btn.textContent = 'Turn on';
          }
        }
        render();
        btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
          var v = null;
          try { v = localStorage.getItem(KEY); } catch (e) {}
          var next = v === 'true' ? 'false' : 'true';
          try { localStorage.setItem(KEY, next); } catch (e) {}
          render();
          if (next === 'true') {
            location.reload();
          }
        });
      } catch (e) {}
    })();
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
